Date:  0/0/1978
Source:  Gold Mining at Waihi
Author:  McARA
Vol / Page:  183
Edition:
Quote:   Two `knocker-lines' of half-inch-diameter wire-rope were installed in each hoisting compartment so that they could easily be reached from any point in the shaft and signals transmitted to the winding-engine driver. <i>ibid.</i> 325 <i>Knocker-lines</i>: Half-inch-diameter wire-ropes suspended in the shaft and used to signal the winding-engine driver.
