Date:  0/0/1986
Source:  Off the Sheep's Back
Author:  RiCHARDS
Vol / Page:  5
Edition:
Quote:  The only other means of communication with the surface [above the goldmine] was primitive. A long wire, known as the `knocker line', extended down the shaft and was accessible at each level. Each pull rang a bell in the winding house.
